Venice Carnival, an annual event held in the iconic city of Venice, Italy, is known for its enchanting masks and elaborate costumes. This tradition dates back to the 12th century and is celebrated in the weeks leading up to Lent. The carnival's masked revellers wander through the city's winding streets and gather in the historic St. Mark's Square for various festivities, including parades, live music, and dance. It's a time when Venice truly comes alive with an air of mystery and intrigue.
